==English==
===Etymology===
[imp. & p. p. {Adapted}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Adapting}.] [L. adaptare; ad + aptare to fit; cf. F. adapter. See {Apt}, {Adept}.]

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌ.dæptˈ/

===Transitive Verb===
To make suitable; to fit, or suit; to adjust; to alter so as to fit for a new use; &mdash; sometimes followed by to or for.